        <div class="side-panel">
            <div class="head">
                Base Model Safety Features</div>
            <div class="links">
                
                        <a href="#ESC" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Electronic Stability Control');">
                            Electronic Stability Control<img src="/Design/Images/feature-noinfo.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="ESC">
                            <img src="/~/media/Images/img-car.jpg" alt="ESC image " title="ESC image "
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Electronic Stability Control (ESC) helps drivers to avoid crashes by reducing the danger of skidding, or losing control as a result of over-steering. Australian research shows that ESC reduces the risk of Single car crashes by 25% find out more ...</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Electronic-Stability-Control/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=electronic stability control&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#FrontSideCurtainAirbags" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Front Side Curtain Airbags ');">
                            Front Side Curtain Airbags <img src="/Design/Images/feature-na.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="FrontSideCurtainAirbags">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Curtain airbags are designed to protect the driver's and front seat passenger's heads in a side impact crash.The curtain airbag activates instantaneously, deploying from the top of the door rails above the side window. They form a cushion between the driver or passenger and the window and stay in place if the car rolls over to protect their head.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Curtain-Side-Airbags-Front/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=curtain side airbags front&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#RearSideCurtainAirbags" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Rear Side Curtain Airbags');">
                            Rear Side Curtain Airbags<img src="/Design/Images/feature-na.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="RearSideCurtainAirbags">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Curtain airbags are designed to protect the driver's and passenger's heads in a crash. The curtain airbag activates instantaneously, deploying from the top of the door rails above the side window. They form a cushion between the driver or passenger and the window and stay in place if the car rolls over to protect their head.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Curtain-Side-Airbags-Rear/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=curtain side airbags rear&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#ActiveCruiseControl" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Active Cruise Control');">
                            Active Cruise Control<img src="/Design/Images/feature-noinfo.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="ActiveCruiseControl">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Also known as Adaptive Cruise Control, Active Cruise Control detects the distance and speed of the preceding vehicle and maintains an appropriate following distance.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Active-Cruise-Control/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=active cruise control&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#TractionControl" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Traction Control');">
                            Traction Control<img src="/Design/Images/feature-na.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="TractionControl">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Traction Control systems optimise grip and stability of the car on the road during acceleration by measuring wheel rotation. It stops wheel spin by reducing engine power or temporarily applying the brakes to that wheel, allowing the car to accelerate smoothly, even on slippery surfaces. Limited slip differentials also help provide a more even distribution of traction forces when the car is on a slippery surface.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Traction-Control/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=traction control&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#AntilockBrakingSystem" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Antilock Braking System');">
                            Antilock Braking System<img src="/Design/Images/feature-optional.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="AntilockBrakingSystem">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>ABS (Antilock Braking System)reduces the risk of tyres skidding under heavy braking and allows the driver to maintain steering control of the car. ABS only operates under heavy braking or on slippery surfaces.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Antilock-Braking-System/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=antilock braking system&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#AdjustableSteeringColumn" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Adjustable Steering Column');">
                            Adjustable Steering Column<img src="/Design/Images/feature-available.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="AdjustableSteeringColumn">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Adjustable steering columns allows for steering wheel heights to be adjusted to the driver’s preference.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Adjustable-Steering-Column/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=adjustable steering column&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#FogLamps" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Fog Lamps');">
                            Fog Lamps<img src="/Design/Images/feature-na.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="FogLamps">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Fog lamps have a low, flat, fan shaped beam designed to improve the driver’s ability to view the road. Fog lamps must only be used in low visibility conditions such as fog or snow.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Fog-Lamps/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=fog lamps&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#FrontAirbagsDriver" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Front Airbags Driver');">
                            Front Airbags Driver<img src="/Design/Images/feature-available.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="FrontAirbagsDriver">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Drivers’ airbags or frontal airbags typically deploy from the steering wheel to protect the driver from striking other parts of the car in a frontal crash. Drivers’ airbags are designed to be used in conjunction with seatbelts and do not offer protection in the event of a side impact crash.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Front-Airbags-Driver/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=front airbags driver&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#FrontAirbagsPassenger" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Front Airbags Passenger');">
                            Front Airbags Passenger<img src="/Design/Images/feature-optional.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="FrontAirbagsPassenger">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Front-Airbags-Passenger/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=front airbags passenger&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#SeatbeltPretensionerDriver" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Seatbelt Pretensioner Driver');">
                            Seatbelt Pretensioner Driver<img src="/Design/Images/feature-available.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="SeatbeltPretensionerDriver">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Pretensioners tighten and reduce slack in seat belts to protect occupants from rapidly moving forward in the event of a crash.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Seatbelt-Pretensioner-Driver/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=seatbelt pretensioner driver&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#SeatbeltPretensionerPassenger" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Seatbelt Pretensioner Passenger');">
                            Seatbelt Pretensioner Passenger<img src="/Design/Images/feature-available.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="SeatbeltPretensionerPassenger">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>Pretensioners tighten and reduce slack in seatbelts to protect occupants from rapidly moving forward in the event of a crash.</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Seatbelt-Pretensioner-Passenger/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=seatbelt pretensioner passenger&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
                        </div>
                    
                        <a href="#SeatbeltRear3Point" class="js_mouseyDialog one" onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackEvent('Safety Features', 'Flyout', 'Seatbelt Rear 3 Point');">
                            Seatbelt Rear 3 Point<img src="/Design/Images/feature-na.png"
                                alt="Safety Option" style="float: right;" /></a>
                        <div id="SeatbeltRear3Point">
                            <img src="/Design/Images/no-image-available.jpg" alt="No image available" title="No image available"
                                width="165" />
                            <br />
                            
		<p>3 point seat belts are belts that goes over the waist (lap) and the shoulder (sash) of the occupant. 3 point seat belts provides better protection than 2 point seat belts (lap belt only).</p>

                            <br />
                            <br />
                            <a href="/Safety-Features/Safety-Features-List/Seatbelt-Rear-3-Point/">Find out more ></a><br />
                            <a href="/Search?feature=seatbelt rear 3 point&featureOnly=true">Search other cars with
                                this Safety Feature ></a>
